  "instructions": [
    "Rinse and soak the lentils in water for about 15 minutes.",
    "Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds and curry leaves. Saute until fragrant.",
    "Add onions and garlic; sauté until translucent.",
    "Stir in celery, tomato sauce, salt, and red chilli powder. Cook until the liquid evaporates slightly.",
    "Fold in the lentils. Season with fennel seeds and saffron threads.",
    "Simmer gently for about 10 minutes or until lentils are tender but not mushy.",
    "Serve hot with a side of raita (coconut yogurt) or chapatis."
